{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d72e337-9291-4f08-adef-213ac3b37e5f","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n\n    // iOS / Mac Catalyst only\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|--------|-------------|\n| App launch | Created → Activated |\n| User switches away | Deactivated → Stopped |\n| User returns | Resumed → Activated |\n| App closed | Stopped → Destroying |\n\nUse `System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine` so output appears in the IDE's debug console without affecting release builds.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"febfdb50-f6cc-4787-b52e-bd22bb0df803","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about subscribing to Window lifecycle events in a .NET MAUI app for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI that I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the `Window` class exposes several lifecycle events that correspond to the app's window state transitions. Let me provide a concise, helpful answer.\n\nThe Window lifecycle events in .NET MAUI are:\n- Created\n- Activated\n- Deactivated\n- Stopped\n- Resumed\n- Destroying\n- Backgrounding (iOS/Mac Catalyst)\n\n\nNow I'll show how to subscribe to these events with a practical example.","outputTokens":505,"requestId":"E84C:16E90D:24E92D1:28F6067:69F93EF8"},"id":"04ef862d-919e-449f-ab48-01b10c949992","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:14.391Z","parentId":"14ee01d5-c896-46a9-9adf-e553e62d4ac7"}
